briefdescription.para: Construct a UsdTyped on the prim held by schemaObj .

detaileddescription.para: Should be preferred over UsdTyped(schemaObj.GetPrim()), as it preserves SchemaBase state.

briefdescription.para: Return a vector of names of all pre-declared attributes for this schema class and all its ancestor classes.

detaileddescription.para: Does not include attributes that may be authored by custom/extended methods of the schemas involved.

briefdescription.para: Returns the kind of schema this class belongs to.
Subclasses may override _IsCompatible to do specific compatibility checking with the given prim, such as type compatibility or value compatibility.

detaileddescription.para: This check is performed when clients invoke the explicit bool operator.

briefdescription.para: The base class for all typed schemas (those that can impart a typeName to a UsdPrim), and therefore the base class for all concrete, instantiable "IsA" schemas.

detaileddescription.para: UsdTyped implements a typeName-based query for its override of UsdSchemaBase::_IsCompatible(). It provides no other behavior.
